                            <comment id="478700" author="gerrit" created="Tue, 18 Nov 2025 21:13:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Manish Regmi &amp;lt;mregmi@ddn.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/62602&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/62602&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19563&quot; title=&quot;Increase default lnet_interfaces_max to 512&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19563&quot;&gt;LU-19563&lt;/a&gt; lnet: Increse the default lnet_interfaces_max&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 44470e883397ddc4163a651c6ec243807102220b&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="478686" author="JIRAUSER19402" created="Tue, 18 Nov 2025 19:30:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looking at the codebase, the only place it uses are related to ping and metadata discovery and its only like 160kb or so for 4K interfaces. So it should be fine if we just make it future proof with like 4096.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;its mostly used in &lt;b&gt;&lt;tt&gt;lnet_extra_bytes_for_md()&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="477071" author="adilger" created="Mon, 3 Nov 2025 17:12:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How much memory is actually used by the NID lists?  If a large number of NIDs is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; used, does this use a lot of memory, or would it be better to increase to 1024 or 4096, so it is well beyond what we actually need that it doesn&apos;t cause problems for the near future.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
